    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.37-39_0001" />
                
                <fw type="curatorial">37</fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>717 <hi rend="caps">E.</hi> 2nd St., Northfield, Minn., Nov.30th, 1922.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Mr. Neihardt:</salute></opener> <p>I am looking forward to a visit from you the first week in February. I thought the surest way to get a visit from you was to book you with your manager. Your formal appearance at Carleton College is the be the evening of Feb. 2nd. We have no lecture course, but we wanted our students to have a chance to hear and meet you. We hope you will be able to allow yourself some time for a visit and that we may <unclear/>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.37-39_0002"/>
                
                    be able to induce you to speak to our students in a more informal way<del/>. And I want some personal visits with you.</p>
                
                <p>Your friend, <hi rend="caps">F.</hi> Horsh, is here. He is making a fine record and I like him very much. He is naturally interested in your coming. Mr. Crafton, professor in the English department, is a warm admirer of yours.</p>
                
                <p>I thought I would write you this note to let you know that we are planning to have you here, so that you can have us in mind.</p>
                
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.9.37-39_0003"/>
                    <fw type="curatorial">39</fw>
                
                <p>We shall probably want you to read "the Song of the Indian Wars" for the <unclear>formal</unclear> occasion. I am glad to see that you have it so nearly ready.</p>
                
                <p>I am glad I shall have this opportunity to see you.</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Sincerely yours,</salute>
                
                    <signed>J.E. Boodin.</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
